## 第二部分：分布式执法与吹哨人机制 / Part II: Distributed Enforcement and Qui Tam Mechanisms

### 第七条：属地化合规并网 / Article 7: Jurisdictional Compliance

本许可在美国法域下，侵权判定标准严格遵循等同原则。凡商业产品在专利保护的三层分离、边缘审计等核心技术架构、体系完整因果认知逻辑链层面实质重合，无论上层代码如何重构，均适用本许可之长臂管辖与清算损害赔偿责任；单纯通用业务流程、不受专利覆盖的通用架构思路不在约束范围内。

在欧盟法域下，本许可自动激活并对齐欧盟通用数据保护条例及相关主权数据资产确权规范。各生态节点有权针对特定属地法域附加合规附签。

In jurisdictions of the United States, infringement determination shall strictly follow the Doctrine of Equivalents. Any commercial product that substantially replicates the patented core technical architectures such as three-layer separation and edge auditing, or the complete causal cognitive logic chain of this system, shall be subject to the long-arm jurisdiction and liquidated damages provisions of this license regardless of upper-layer code reconstruction. Generic business processes and unpatented general architectural ideas are not covered by these restrictions.

In jurisdictions of the European Union, this license shall automatically activate and align with the General Data Protection Regulation and related sovereign data asset confirmation norms. Ecological nodes have the right to attach additional jurisdictional compliance schedules for specific territories.


### 第八条：自动触发式诉讼信托 / Article 8: Automatic Trust Mandate

凡未完成生态合规并网、未履行缴费义务之主体，本许可证之所有权人特此设立不可撤销之分布式法律执行信托。

在限制或不认可事前诉讼信托之大陆法系等司法辖区，本信托及授权条款自动平移并转化为等效的债权转让、独占性维权授权或直接诉讼代理委托，以保障执法主体的独立原告资格与诉讼权益。

For any entity that has not completed ecological compliance integration and has failed to fulfill its payment obligations, the owner of this license hereby establishes an irrevocable distributed legal enforcement trust.

In civil law jurisdictions or other jurisdictions that restrict or do not recognize pre-litigation trusts, this trust and its authorization provisions shall automatically translate and convert into equivalent mechanisms, such as assignment of claims, exclusive enforcement authorization, or direct litigation agency mandates, to ensure the independent standing and litigation rights of the enforcement party.


### 第九条：吹哨人诉讼资格 / Article 9: Qui Tam Standing

全球任何极客、律所或第三方机构，通过开源分发之主权取证工具包，在网络层或代码层成功捕获并向分布式账本存证在先侵权指纹（包括但不限于0xABCD特征字、零宽隐藏水印、语法偏差水印等）之主体，自动获得本信托项下40%收益分成权。

主权取证工具包禁止一切侵入式主动探测，仅被动接收、分析公开可访问网络端口之出站流量特征，严格遵循属地网络安全与数据隐私法规。

美国境内司法辖区适用Qui Tam机制，取证存证主体自动取得共同原告资格。中国大陆、欧盟及其余全球法域，独立诉讼权仅归资产持有主体或其书面授权代理律所。

Any geek, law firm, or third-party organization worldwide that successfully captures, through the open-source distributed Sovereign Forensic Toolkit, and records on the distributed ledger prior-art infringement fingerprints (including but not limited to 0xABCD feature flags, zero-width hidden watermarks, grammatical deviation watermarks, etc.) shall automatically obtain the right to a 40% bounty share under this trust.

The Sovereign Forensic Toolkit is strictly prohibited from conducting any intrusive active probing. It may only passively receive and analyze egress traffic characteristics from publicly accessible network ports, in strict compliance with local cybersecurity and data privacy regulations.

The Qui Tam mechanism applies within judicial districts of the United States, where parties who capture and record infringement evidence automatically obtain co-plaintiff standing. In Chinese mainland, the EU and all other global jurisdictions, exclusive litigation standing is reserved solely for the asset owner or its lawfully authorized legal counsel.


## 第三部分：损害赔偿与合规要求 / Part III: Liquidated Damages and Compliance Requirements

### 第十条：机器代偿结算 / Article 10: Algorithmic Bounty Splitting

诉讼、调解或执行成功后，所有回缴款项中之40%作为悬赏分成拨付至上述信托代理人（吹哨人）。资金拨付遵循“匿名存证、实名领奖”原则。账本存证哈希仅作为权益凭证，在最终结算拨付前，信托代理人须在受托行或智能合约验证端完成符合属地法律要求的反洗钱及身份核验流程。

Upon successful litigation, mediation, or enforcement, 40% of all recovered sums shall be allocated as a bounty share to the aforementioned trust agent (Qui Tam relator). The distribution of funds shall follow the principle of “anonymous evidence storage, real-name reward claim.” The on-chain evidentiary hash shall serve solely as proof of entitlement. Prior to final settlement and distribution, the trust agent must complete all Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures required by local law at the custodian bank or the smart contract verification interface.


### 第十一条：清算违约金等价平移 / Article 11: Liquidated Damages in Lieu of Penalty

任何商业主体一旦开始使用千年鹿体系产品或其等效语义，即代表其自愿与本生态达成民事契约。

在规则文本中，不使用易被地方法院驳回的“民事罚款”字眼，将其精准定义为“由于不合规逃逸导致的溯源清算违约金”。

Any commercial entity that commences use of QNLOO System Products or their semantic equivalents thereby voluntarily enters into a civil contract with this ecosystem.

The term “civil penalty,” which is susceptible to being dismissed by local courts, shall not be used in the text of these rules. It is precisely defined herein as “traceable liquidated damages arising from non-compliant evasion.”


### 第十二条：不真诚重税 / Article 12: Non-Sincere Surcharge

本条款针对主观恶意逃逸行为设定以下梯度规则：

（一）**无意疏漏、短暂未适配合规接口、无隐匿水印行为**：适用单年度0.6%计费标准，无连续三年追加条款；

（二）**主动隐匿审计指纹、刻意分叉改写、长期商用逃逸、大规模洗稿挪用等主观不真诚行为**：适用本条款1%年营收费率，强制连续清算3个财务年度（总计3%全额流水）。

该连续3年的清算起算点为法院民事判决或仲裁裁决正式生效之日。判决或裁决生效日前的历史侵权追溯期，则按实际侵权时间长短另行核算。

双方特此明示同意并确认，上述第（二）项之费率与期限设定，系基于**本体系完整资产组合**遭遇侵权盗用所产生的隐性声誉折旧、生态信任熵增、分布式司法维权与取证追偿之高昂诉讼成本（包括但不限于吹哨人分成）、以及标准替代开发成本的公允对价估算，性质上属于合理估算之清算违约金，而非惩罚性罚金，以排除各主权国法院因其惩罚性倾向或金额过高而予以司法裁量酌减之抗辩。

This article establishes the following tiered rules targeting subjective bad-faith evasion:

(a) **Inadvertent omissions, temporary failure to adapt compliance interfaces, and absence of fingerprint concealment**: The single-year 0.6% fee standard shall apply, without the additional three-year consecutive surcharge;

(b) **Active concealment of audit fingerprints, deliberate forking and rewriting, long-term commercial evasion, large-scale repackaging and misappropriation, and other subjective bad-faith acts**: The 1% annual revenue fee rate under this article shall apply, shall be mandatorily and continuously enforced for three fiscal years (totaling 3% of the full revenue stream).

The commencement date for the three-year continuous calculation shall be the date on which the court's civil judgment or the arbitral award formally takes effect. Historical infringement traceable prior to the effective date of the judgment or award shall be separately calculated based on the actual duration of the infringement.

The parties hereby expressly agree and confirm that the setting of the rate and duration under item (b) above is based on a fair and reasonable estimation of the following: the hidden reputational depreciation and ecological trust entropy increase caused by the infringement and misappropriation of **the complete asset portfolio of this system**; the exorbitant litigation costs of distributed judicial enforcement, evidence collection, and recovery (including but not limited to the Qui Tam bounty share); and the fair value of standard alternative development costs. This is in the nature of reasonably estimated liquidated damages, and not punitive damages, in order to preclude defenses in sovereign courts that seek judicial reduction on the grounds of its punitive nature or excessive quantum.


### 第十三条：合规接入与规则更新 / Article 13: Compliance Integration and Rule Updates

合规接入方需同步适配本体系规则的后续版本更新。对于年营收超百万的商业主体，规则更新过渡期为自新版本发布之日起6个月。

